Verifying this using trigonometric identities and exact values confirms that the exact value is indeed \(-\sqrt{3}\). Therefore, the simplified form of \(\tan 100^\circ + 4 \sin 100^\circ\) is: \[ \boxed{-\sqrt{3}} \]
